\\\",\\\"section\\\",null,{\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"font-[Epilogue] text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Overview\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-on-surface-variant text-sm whitespace-pre-line\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"The Mirror Hall is a hidden location in The Freak Circus that only appears under specific conditions. It contains seven mirrors, each showing events from different routes, future scenes, and occasionally the player's desktop. The Hall is considered the most lore-rich location in the game because it reveals information that cannot be found through normal gameplay.\\\"}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"section\\\",null,{\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"font-[Epilogue] text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Historical Record\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-on-surface-variant text-sm whitespace-pre-line\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"The Mirror Hall was constructed in Year 5 of the circus's timeline as part of the rebuilt facility. According to The Doctor's files, the mirrors were designed to show 'different versions of reality' — reflecting the project's goal of preserving multiple consciousness states simultaneously. The Hall's geometry does not match the circus's floor plan, suggesting it exists in a space that should be outside the building's boundaries.\\\"}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"section\\\",null,{\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"font-[Epilogue] text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Evidence\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-on-surface-variant text-sm whitespace-pre-line\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"1. The Hall only appears after failing at least one route. 2. Contains 7 mirrors showing different route events. 3. The central mirror shows the player's desktop, breaking the fourth wall. 4. Mirror reflections change based on the number of completed endings. 5. Audio files contain breathing sounds not matching any character. 6. Some players report seeing a sixth performer in the mirrors.\\\"}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"section\\\",null,{\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"font-[Epilogue] text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Related Characters\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-on-surface-variant text-sm whitespace-pre-line\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"• Pierrot: Sees the player in mirrors instead of his own reflection. • Columbina: The Hall is the primary setting for her route. • The Doctor: Designed the mirrors as part of Project Continuity. • Null Performer: Some theorists believe this entity is visible only in mirrors.\\\"}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"section\\\",null,{\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"font-[Epilogue] text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Related Endings\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-on-surface-variant text-sm whitespace-pre-line\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"• Eternal Silence: The Hall is the final location in this ending. • Corrupted Data: Contains references to 'Mirror Loop #7' in unused files. • Columbina's Truth: The fourth door in her hallway leads to a room of mirrors.\\\"}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"section\\\",null,{\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"font-[Epilogue] text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Related Theories\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-on-surface-variant text-sm whitespace-pre-line\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"• Mirror Identity: The mirrors show that the player is not the same person across routes. • Replay Awareness: Characters who look in mirrors remember previous playthroughs. • Purgatorial System: The Hall is a judgment room where performers see their past actions.\\\"}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"section\\\",null,{\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"font-[Epilogue] text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Community Debate\\\"}],\\\"$Le\\\"]}],\\\"$Lf\\\",\\\"$L10\\\"]}]\\n\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"7:[\\\"$\\\",\\\"footer\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"bg-surface border-t border-outline/10 w-full\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 md:px-16 py-6 flex flex-col md:flex-row justify-between items-center gap-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"flex items-center gap-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"img\\\",null,{\\\"src\\\":\\\"/favicon-32x32.png\\\",\\\"alt\\\":\\\"Freak Circus Hub\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"w-8 h-8 rounded-sm\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"font-[Epilogue] text-lg font-bold text-foreground\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"FREAK CIRCUS HUB\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"font-[JetBrains_Mono] text-xs text-on-surface-variant opacity-60\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"© 2026\\\"}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-xs text-on-surface-variant opacity-60 text-center max-w-md\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"Not affiliated with the original game or its developers. All trademarks belong to their respective owners.\\\",\\\" \\\",[\\\"$\\\",\\\"a\\\",null,{\\\"href\\\":\\\"mailto:hello@freak-circus.com\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"underline hover:text-primary transition-colors\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Contact us for removal requests\\\"}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"flex gap-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L11\\\",null,{\\\"href\\\":\\\"/privacy-policy\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"font-[JetBrains_Mono] text-xs uppercase text-on-surface-variant opacity-60 hover:text-primary transition-colors\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Privacy\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L11\\\",null,{\\\"href\\\":\\\"/terms-of-service\\\",\\\"className\\